- get_integration_schema(type, provider)
- validate_config(type, provider, config)

WebhookService methods:
- create_endpoint()
- list_endpoints()
- update_endpoint()
- delete_endpoint()
- deliver_event()
- list_deliveries()
- retry_delivery()

Rules:
- Dry-run by default.
- Webhook signing secret must never be returned.
- Payload must be DLP-scanned before delivery.
- Webhook delivery failure must not crash system.
- Event payloads must be redacted.

SIEM adapters:
- MockSIEMAdapter
- GenericHTTP SIEM shell

Methods:
- export_events(events, dry_run=True) -> SIEMExportResult

Rules:
- Dry-run by default.
- No secrets in export payload.
- Real export requires SIEM endpoint and token.

Ticketing adapters:
- MockTicketingAdapter
- GenericTicketingAdapter shell

Methods:
- create_ticket(title, description, severity, metadata) -> Ticket
- update_ticket(ticket_id, patch) -> Ticket

SSO adapters:
- MockSSOAdapter
- OIDCAdapter shell
- SAMLAdapter shell

Rules:
- SSO disabled by default.
- OIDC/SAML real config must be explicit.
- SSO callback must not accept unsigned/unverified payloads.
- This phase may implement shell endpoints and config validation, not full provider-specific SSO.

SCIM service:
- create_user_from_scim()
- update_user_from_scim()
- deactivate_user_from_scim()
- list_scim_users()

Rules:
- Disabled by default.
- SCIM token must not be logged.
- Tenant-scoped provisioning.
- SCIM actions audited.

